title: For Sale:  Remington Fieldmaster model 572 (.Slide Action / Cross-Bolt Safety)
postcontent:
The Remington 572 Fieldmaster was introduced in 1955 and was manufactured by the Remington Arms Company (NY,NY).   It is noted for its similarity to the Remington 870 shotgun in design, and for being chambered in the ubiquitous .22 Long Rifle cartridge as well as the less popular (and less well known) .22 Short and .22 Long cartridges.  

The rifle features a cross-bolt safety and the receiver is factory grooved for scope mounts.  The tube-fed magazine under the barrel holds 15 rounds of .22LR or 22 rounds of .22S.  This model of rifle has remained popular over the years for both its reliability and accuracy.  I've had this one since I was a kid and it has help thin rabbit and squirrel populations here in the Midwest.  

Based on what I found online (Remington Society of America) this rifle appears to be manufactured in March of 1978.  This rifle has a couple spots of surface rust (which I've oiled and cleaned) and the normal bumps as bruises normally found on a field rifle.   Based on the condition, I have priced it accordingly.

More information can be found on Remington's 572 homepage: http://www.remington.com/products/firearms/rimfire/model-572/model-572-bdl-fieldmaster.aspx

title: For Sale:  EOTech EXPS3-0
postcontent:
The EOTech EXPS3-0 has all the great features that EOTech Holographic Weapon Sights are known for in a significantly more compact package. This optic features a 7mm raised base for better iron sight access, and an adjustable quick-detach lever for easy and repeatable attachment and removal. The more compact design only requires 2.75" of rail space!

The compact design used by the XPS and EXPS models was created by separating the battery compartment from the base and mounting it transversely. This not only dramatically decreases the over-all size of the optic, but allows the battery compartment to easily clear the delta ring on M4/M16 platform carbines and rifles.

The A65/1 reticle features a 65MOA circle for fast target acquisition in CQB scenarios with a 1MOA aiming dot for precise shooting to mid ranges.

The EXPS3 series are night vision compatible.

10 Night Vision compatible settings!
Transmission holography allows for a parallax free optic with unlimited eye relief
Highly versatile reticle allows for fast CQC work and precise fire out to medium ranges.
Rugged design with shatterproof glass and aluminum hood assembly.
7mm raised base for unobstructed co-witnessing.
Battery sits perpendicular to the optic giving a much more compact size, only requires 2.75" of rail space.

Mounts easily to any 1" Weaver or M1913 picatinny rail.
600 hour continuous use battery life on setting 12 with 1x CR123 lithium battery
Waterproof to 10ft.
